=Description=

"The mobility sector is undergoing a profound transformation. Urbanization, demographic changes and environmental factors are bringing on challenges, which are requiring governments and private transport services to rethink their approaches to mobility in an intermodal way. Mobility experts working in ridesharing, peer-to-peer carsharing and service design tell us their visions of the future of shared mobility."

Speakers: Markus Barnikel (CEO, Carpooling), Mar Alarcon (Founder, Social Car), Guillaume Verhaeghe (Founder, Djengo), Aashild Stav (Service Designer, Utilisacteurs)
Moderator: Francesca Pick (OuiShare)



